rComments: horrible lecturer, her lectures do not draw on the readings at all. Shes tries to shove way too much info into each two hour lecture. She refuses to post her slides on blackboard and moves through them so fast that you cannot write the info down. She's not personable or friendly and this course is more of a history course than religion.

Course load was aweful but I nonetheless enjoyed the course and the professor.  She does pick her favorites, so suck up and go to office hours if you want a good mark.  Even if you study for her exams with all you got, you will not succeed.
oh my god. it was ridiculous. the reading was totally unreasonable (entire books for one week?!?!) and surprise quizzes. what is this, grade four?

A complete waste of time & money! Class did not reflect description in time-table. Lectures were very brief and most time was given to presentations which were designed to be completely unacademic charades. The university should not offer this course.
